1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,933
You know if only God
could grant me one wish,

2
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,167
I'll ask for our daughter back.

3
00:00:16,233 --> 00:00:17,700
I just want to see her
one more time.

4
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,500
- Hey!
- What happened?

5
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,733
What are you doing in my office?

6
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,633
You said Mookie's been sick
since she was a child.

7
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,067
If that medical report was
from ten years ago,

8
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,000
does that mean that you lied?

9
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:39,067
Do you honestly believe
that I can harm my own child?

10
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:42,333
Why on earth would I do
such a thing, Astrid?

11
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:46,000
It will distract you
from thinking about Kyla.

12
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:47,233
You have a point.

13
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:50,533
That's the reason why
we came here, to forget.

14
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:52,100
You'll get better if you
take the medicines

15
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:55,267
I've been giving you.
I know what's best for you.

16
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:35,433
Ma'am, I'm feeling
a little depressed.

17
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:41,000
We need to take care
of our mental health too, right?

18
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,800
What mental health
are you talking about?

19
00:01:47,967 --> 00:01:49,567
Go ahead,

20
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:51,333
you can take a vacation.

21
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,633
Thank you, Ma'am.

22
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,667
- Forever.
- What?

23
00:01:54,733 --> 00:02:00,267
Take your leave, because you
don't have a job to return to.

24
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:01,267
Ma'am...

25
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,200
I'm fired?

26
00:02:03,267 --> 00:02:04,567
Oh no.

27
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:06,600
Now I feel...

28
00:02:06,667 --> 00:02:08,700
more depressed.

29
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:13,400
Go on, take care
of your mental health.

30
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,467
Leave!

31
00:02:16,933 --> 00:02:17,933
Right now!

32
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:25,800
Ma'am...

33
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:29,267
Ma'am, why did you fire Malou?

34
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:30,967
There's a lot of work
that needs to be done here.

35
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:32,867
I can't do it on my own.

36
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,167
Don't worry,

37
00:02:37,567 --> 00:02:40,267
I'll increase your salary,

38
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:43,067
just take good care of Mookie.

39
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:44,633
Thank you, Ma'am.

40
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,300
But that's what
I'm trying to tell you.

41
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:50,800
I need to take care of Mookie,
and the laundry is piling up.

42
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:55,600
Perhaps we can get more help,
someone who can do the laundry.

43
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:57,000
Take care of it then.

44
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:59,400
If that's what you want,
then do something about it.

45
00:02:59,467 --> 00:03:01,433
What's important to me is...

46
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:02,733
you keep an eye on my daughter.

47
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,167
Okay, Ma'am.

48
00:03:04,233 --> 00:03:05,500
Thank you.

49
00:03:05,567 --> 00:03:07,067
Thank you, Ma'am.

50
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:16,167
Oh really?
So what's going to happen now?

51
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:18,433
This is my last card.

52
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,300
- What now?
- Oh wow!

53
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:23,533
- Awesome!
- You're so lucky, Ligaya!

54
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,367
Well, aren't you glad
I gave you some money.

55
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:27,667
Thank you.

56
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:33,100
You know, my mom told me that
the moment I took my first step

57
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:35,000
I went and grabbed cards.

58
00:03:35,067 --> 00:03:41,300
Oh wow, just admit that
you like to grab things!

59
00:03:41,367 --> 00:03:43,333
That led you to have your child!

60
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,567
Why are you
messing with me, Wiro!

61
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:50,000
Hey, we're best friends now,
okay?

62
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:51,167
Are you sure?

63
00:03:51,233 --> 00:03:53,167
But I just moved here.

64
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,167
That's all right.

65
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:58,733
I got you whenever
you want to gamble.

66
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,167
- You're my new best friend!
- Right?

67
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:03,800
- Give me that luck!
- Right, BFF!

68
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:06,233
Right?

69
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:08,100
- Okay let's play another game.
- Okay, game!

70
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:09,167
Kutsy!

71
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:11,267
- Wait for a minute, Kutsy!
- Hey.

72
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,533
Looks like you're having fun.

73
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,233
- Sorry to bother you.
- It's okay.

74
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,800
I just want to ask you
if you know someone

75
00:04:16,867 --> 00:04:19,567
who can do laundry,
she doesn't need to stay in.

76
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:23,200
Oh my, did you lose
a helper again?

77
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:23,967
We did.

78
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:25,900
Come on, you might know someone.

79
00:04:25,967 --> 00:04:27,800
I'm getting tired, I can't deal
with the laundry too.

80
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:30,267
I have a lot on my plate.

81
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:33,067
- Come on.
- Miss, be quiet.

82
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:35,100
I have the solution
to your problem.

83
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:36,033
Okay?

84
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:38,167
- What's your name?
- I'm Flor.

85
00:04:38,233 --> 00:04:39,700
You know someone
who can do the laundry?

86
00:04:39,767 --> 00:04:40,800
My daughter.

87
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:43,467
That's her specialty.
She's good at that job.

88
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,900
Kutsy, do you know her?

89
00:04:45,967 --> 00:04:47,833
- BFF.
- Yes, I do.

90
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:50,933
Go ahead, employ her daughter.

91
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,733
All right, as long as
she's a good person.

92
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,833
She's not just kind.

93
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:58,133
She's very kind,
she didn't take after me.

94
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,633
Perfect!

95
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:02,767
- Thank you, Kutsy. Thank you.
- Okay, let's continue.

96
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:05,500
- Can I get an advance pay?
- I'm not the employer.

97
00:05:05,567 --> 00:05:08,133
I'm just the maid.
I don't have money.

98
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:11,300
You found a job for me, Mom?

99
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:12,300
I did!

100
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:15,633
I boosted you up!

101
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:19,200
I'm glad my new best friend
backed me up.

102
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:24,033
My friend Kutsy
and her nephew Wiro.

103
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:27,433
See? I have awesome new friends!

104
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:30,800
So now you got a job
as a laundry woman.

105
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:33,833
Okay, let's pray before we eat.

106
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,933
Thank you for protecting us
everyday.

107
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:38,433
In the name of Jesus Christ,

108
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:41,233
- Amen.
- Amen.

109
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:44,067
So where is she going to work?

110
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:49,800
Remember that big house
we saw on our way here?

111
00:05:49,867 --> 00:05:53,633
The house that gave me
goosebumps.

112
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:54,667
That one!

113
00:05:54,733 --> 00:05:57,600
But Kutsy told me
that the house is fine.

114
00:05:57,667 --> 00:06:01,133
It's just that your employer
is a bit weird.

115
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:03,533
Why did she say that?

116
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:07,600
She said she doesn't let
her daughter out.

117
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,967
She has a sickly daughter.

118
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:12,533
But don't meddle
with their affairs.

119
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,800
You're just their laundry woman,

120
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:17,300
you have a job now,
that's what matters. Right?

121
00:06:21,267 --> 00:06:24,867
Don't I get a thank you?

122
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:29,067
I used my skills
to get you a job.

123
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:30,933
Thank you, Mom.

124
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,033
You're welcome.

125
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,800
- Flor.
- Yes?

126
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,467
Thank you,

127
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:45,733
for letting me stay here.

128
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,933
Oh no, it's just this once,

129
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,033
while I'm waiting for the gas
to get delivered.

130
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:53,767
No one will watch you
inside the house.

131
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,367
But...

132
00:06:55,433 --> 00:06:58,100
we'll have to go inside
once the delivery gets here.

133
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,533
Okay?

134
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,067
- Okay.
- Okay.

135
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:08,100
- Do you feel hot?
- A little, but..

136
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:11,733
It's here! Wait here, okay?
I'll be right back.

137
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,433
Hi, Sir.

138
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,633
Oh, come in.

139
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,533
Okay, Sir. Hey, wait here.

140
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,833
Stay here, this won't take long.

141
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,033
He'll just bring this inside.

142
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,333
There, there!

143
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,433
There! I got you!

144
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,667
- Look!
- There, there.

145
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:35,533
Go on, shoot it!
You have to kill it!

146
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,000
Get it wet!

147
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:38,900
Go on! There you go!
It can't fly off now!

148
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:40,867
Hurry up! There you go!

149
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:43,667
Go on!

150
00:07:43,733 --> 00:07:45,633
Get it wet,
so it can't fly off.

151
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,200
Hey!

152
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,700
Hey, don't do that
to the poor bird!

153
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:51,267
Don't do that!

154
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,267
Oh my God!

155
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,000
The weirdo!

156
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:58,400
Why are you butting in?

157
00:07:58,467 --> 00:08:01,400
Or perhaps you want to be
like that bird.

158
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:05,733
Because you're a prisoner
in your own house.

159
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:11,700
And now tied in a wheelchair.

160
00:08:11,767 --> 00:08:12,867
You know what?

161
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:17,167
You can't fly no matter
what you try to do.

162
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:19,033
Don't worry, we'll let you fly.

163
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,267
Is that what you want?

164
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:28,967
- You want to fly, right?
- Hey, wait!

165
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:30,400
Wait, where are you taking me?

166
00:08:30,467 --> 00:08:32,833
- Be quiet.
- Hey! Flor!

167
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,333
- What are you doing?
- Hush!

168
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,400
Hey, stop!

169
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:39,133
Don't worry,
you're not going anywhere!

170
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:43,067
- Hey! Stop!
- What will you do to me?

171
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:45,333
Don't worry.
We're not going to do anything!

172
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:48,300
Please, take me back home!
Please.

173
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:50,233
- No, you got this!
- I need to...

174
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,767
- I need to go home to my mom.
- No.

175
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:54,533
- She'll get mad at me. Please.
- It's nice out here.

176
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:59,367
Don't you want to be here?
Look it's nice here.

177
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:02,467
Please! Please. Please,
take me back home.

178
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:04,867
Hey! What...

179
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:06,667
Here, right here.

180
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:09,033
- There, stay here alone.
- Hey!

181
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:11,467
Stop!

182
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:15,167
- Here, you should stay here.
- Hey!

183
00:09:15,233 --> 00:09:16,867
It's better over here.

184
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:21,133
- Stop!
- There.

185
00:09:23,133 --> 00:09:26,033
That was hard!

186
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,833
Don't you like it here?

187
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:29,067
It's nice out here.

188
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:32,833
What are you doing?
I said, bring me back to my mom.

189
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,967
Then go home by yourself!

190
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:36,267
You can do it!

191
00:09:37,633 --> 00:09:39,000
- Let's go.
- Hey!

192
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:41,300
Hey, don't leave me here!

193
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:08,067
Wow!

194
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:16,100
Wow.

195
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,933
It's so nice out here.

196
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:35,000
This is the best day ever!

197
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,167
Oh no, the kid!

198
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:03,200
Hey.

199
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:05,500
Are you hurt?

200
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:06,967
- Oh no.
- It hurts.

201
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:12,833
Does it hurt?

202
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,533
- Not anymore.
- No more pain?

203
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,433
Okay, can you get up?

204
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,833
Slowly.

205
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,300
Who are you with?

206
00:11:20,367 --> 00:11:22,500
- My mom.
- Where is she?

207
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:24,167
I don't know where she is.

208
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:25,733
What do you want?
Do you want something?

209
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,667
- I want ice cream.
- Ice cream.

210
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:30,933
Over there. Come on,
I'll buy you ice cream.

211
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:34,700
Who else is with you?

212
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:36,033
No one else.

213
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,633
No one else?

214
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:40,467
Don't worry we'll find your mom.

215
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,900
Sir, once ice cream please.

216
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,067
Yes.

217
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:54,867
There you are!

218
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:57,300
Why are you getting ice cream?

219
00:11:57,367 --> 00:11:58,467
I got it for him.

220
00:11:58,533 --> 00:12:00,300
I'm sorry about that,
I saw him when he fell down.

221
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:02,933
Just tend to his wounds.

222
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,333
Thank you.

223
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,700
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

224
00:12:21,967 --> 00:12:23,133
Miss?

225
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:30,633
Miss!

226
00:12:35,167 --> 00:12:36,167
Miss!

227
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:38,933
Miss!

228
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,700
- Miss!
- Mookie!

229
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:43,400
Mookie!

230
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:46,300
Are you okay?

231
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:51,433
Mookie?
What are you doing out here?

232
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,500
Mommy!

233
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:53,800
- Mommy!
- I knew it!

234
00:12:53,867 --> 00:12:56,600
This boy is not
a good influence on you!

235
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:58,300
Mommy, no! No! Mommy!

236
00:12:58,367 --> 00:13:00,967
- Explain yourself at home!
- Mommy, I'm sorry.

237
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:02,500
Mommy, let me explain.

238
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:04,600
You're so stubborn!

239
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,400
You're the only
psychiatrist I trust, Doc,

240
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:58,900
that's why I came here
to see you.

241
00:13:58,967 --> 00:14:02,833
I'm worried about a person
I know and her child.

242
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:04,267
Are you related to her?

243
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:05,700
I can give her some advice

244
00:14:05,767 --> 00:14:08,567
but better still
if I can see her personally.

245
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:10,533
I don't think she'll want
to consult with you,

246
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,367
that's the problem,

247
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:14,100
But she told me

248
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:16,733
her daughter has been sick
since she was a child.

249
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,267
But oddly,

250
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,567
she doesn't want to bring
her daughter to the hospital.

251
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:21,767
Instead,

252
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:24,867
she administers the medication
and treatment herself.

253
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:26,000
And then?

254
00:14:26,067 --> 00:14:28,100
Mommy, please. I'm sorry.

255
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:32,300
Mommy, Mommy!

256
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:34,100
I raised you,
and I cared for you,

257
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:36,667
but you always defy me!

258
00:14:36,733 --> 00:14:39,400
I didn't do that to my parents!

259
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:42,400
I do everything
they want me to do!

260
00:14:42,467 --> 00:14:49,067
I did everything
so they'll accept me!

261
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:51,767
So they'll appreciate me!

262
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:53,367
So they'll love me!

263
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:57,400
So they'll be proud of me!

264
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:01,200
But no!

265
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:04,467
I have a strong feeling

266
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:07,167
that she's fabricating
her daughter's illness.

267
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:14,400
Do you think that it can be
Munchausen Syndrome By Proxy?

268
00:15:14,467 --> 00:15:16,167
I read about it on the internet,

269
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:19,667
and she's showing
consistent behaviour.

270
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:22,267
We cannot say that
conclusively, Astrid.

271
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:24,733
There are a wide array
of psychiatric illnesses

272
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,900
that we can't diagnose.

273
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:31,600
But, not unless I can see
her history.

274
00:15:31,667 --> 00:15:36,333
All of it, all that
I did, it's all useless!

275
00:15:36,433 --> 00:15:41,033
They think I'm useless!

276
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:43,533
I'm nothing!

277
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:48,667
But in the case of Munchausen
Syndrome By Proxy or MSBP.

278
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:51,567
It's a psychiatric disorder
that needs treatment

279
00:15:51,633 --> 00:15:53,300
because of its rare complexity,

280
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:55,333
personality traits,
and backgrounds.

281
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,367
There is faking of the
illness of a child

282
00:15:57,433 --> 00:15:59,667
for fear of abandonment
and being alone

283
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:01,567
and feeling rejected.

284
00:16:01,633 --> 00:16:02,967
They're gone...

285
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:09,500
and I didn't even feel
like they loved me.

286
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:21,767
They're gone and I didn't even
know if I made them proud.

287
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:27,733
Perhaps...

288
00:16:29,267 --> 00:16:35,933
Perhaps I'm useless,
that's why they can't love me.

289
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:40,700
But...

290
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:47,433
I'm a good doctor, right?

291
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:50,667
Or she could have severe
abandonment issues.

292
00:16:50,733 --> 00:16:54,633
Or even a history of unresolved
issues and trauma.

293
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:56,833
Her parents died.

294
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:59,133
Her boyfriend abandoned her.

295
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:02,000
But the worst thing
that happened to her

296
00:17:02,067 --> 00:17:05,167
is when her child died
in an accident.

297
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:07,933
All of them abandoned me!

298
00:17:09,767 --> 00:17:12,067
My parents abandoned me!

299
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:13,667
And your dad!

300
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,633
And my child!

301
00:17:21,867 --> 00:17:24,400
They all left me...

302
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:30,000
but I rise up.

303
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,300
I rise up!

304
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:34,833
I endured everything!

305
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:38,233
And this...

306
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:41,533
I'm doing it for you!

307
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:45,200
Because I don't want you to go
through what I've been through.

308
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:49,000
But no matter what I do,
you always disobey me!

309
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,000
Mommy, no. No, Mommy.

310
00:17:51,067 --> 00:17:56,833
I'm sorry, please.
Mommy, I'm sorry.

311
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:01,500
I tried to discipline you.

312
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:04,833
But you never learn.

313
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:06,733
Perhaps this time,

314
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,700
with what I'm about to do now,

315
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:11,133
you will learn your lesson.

316
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,467
Mommy? Mommy?

317
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,400
Mommy, what are you going to do?

318
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:16,733
Mommy!

319
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,833
Mommy, no!

320
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:22,700
No, Mommy! No! Mommy!

321
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,900
Mommy! No!

322
00:18:24,967 --> 00:18:26,800
No, Mommy! Please!

323
00:18:26,867 --> 00:18:29,933
Let me out of here, Mommy.

324
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,200
Mommy, please. I promise
I won't go outside anymore.

325
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:36,667
Please, Mommy. Mommy, please.

326
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:40,467
Plese, don't lock me up
in this room!

327
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:44,300
All my life, I've been locked
up in this house!

328
00:18:44,367 --> 00:18:46,600
Mommy!

329
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:48,567
You're not going anywhere.

330
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:52,967
Mommy, please!

331
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:57,433
Mommy, please let me out, Mommy!

332
00:18:57,533 --> 00:19:00,267
Mommy!

333
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,633
Mommy!

334
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,900
Mommy!

335
00:19:11,167 --> 00:19:13,800
Mommy, please!

336
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:23,900
Please, Mommy! Mommy!

337
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:28,367
Mommy!

338
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:30,433
Mommy!

339
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,333
Mommy! Mommy!

340
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:36,867
Mommy!

341
00:19:42,233 --> 00:19:44,267
Mommy!

342
00:19:45,533 --> 00:19:48,200
Mommy.

343
00:19:59,867 --> 00:20:05,367
Mommy!

344
00:20:05,467 --> 00:20:08,533
Mommy!

345
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:14,433
Mommy!

346
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:21,267
Mommy.

347
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:29,333
Perhaps she's a mother too.

348
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,133
That's why she cared
for that boy

349
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,200
even though he's not related
to her.

350
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:35,167
I wish I were that child.

351
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:43,000
Why didn't you care
for me like that?

352
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:46,167
I wish you were like her.

353
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:50,067
Mommy...

354
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:53,300
but you're not like her.

355
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:58,633
I wish, someone like her
will come for me.

356
00:21:01,433 --> 00:21:07,600
Someone who will make me
feel loved by a mother.

357
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:26,800
Mommy, please.

358
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:29,667
Mommy, I don't want to be here!

359
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:33,100
Mommy!

360
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:37,633
Where are you?

361
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:40,933
Mommy!

362
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:46,433
Why are you doing this to me!

363
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:48,600
Why, Mommy!

364
00:21:50,667 --> 00:21:52,200
Who are you? Why are you here?

365
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:55,167
You can't be here!
You're trespassing!

366
00:21:55,233 --> 00:21:56,800
Get out! Get out of here!

367
00:21:56,867 --> 00:21:57,833
Wait a minute.

368
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:01,700
Are you Emma? Ligaya's daughter?

369
00:22:01,767 --> 00:22:03,000
Yes, I'm Emma.

370
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:06,467
My mom told me that
I will start working today.

371
00:22:06,533 --> 00:22:09,400
That's right,
you work 3 days a week.

372
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:11,367
You go home after work hours.
You get free meals,

373
00:22:11,433 --> 00:22:14,700
and you get paid every 15th
and end of the month.

374
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,167
Does that sound good?

375
00:22:16,233 --> 00:22:18,533
- Yes.
- And keep this in mind,

376
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:22,467
you are not allowed
to go inside the mansion, okay?

377
00:22:22,533 --> 00:22:24,967
You stay in the laundry area
and kitchen.

378
00:22:25,033 --> 00:22:26,433
Is that clear?

379
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,433
Yes.

380
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:31,400
I haven't told my employer
about you yet.

381
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:34,500
So please stay out of her sight.

382
00:22:34,567 --> 00:22:36,867
Okay?

383
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:37,700
Yes.

384
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:41,833
If you don't mind me asking,

385
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:45,500
I heard someone crying
over that way.

386
00:22:45,567 --> 00:22:47,100
Do you know who that is?

387
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,533
That's Mookie.

388
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,367
Ma'am Olive's daughter.

389
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:53,700
She got reprimanded.

390
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,067
If you want to keep
your job here,

391
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:59,033
keep out of their business.

392
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:02,633
Everything you see here,
stays here.

393
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:03,800
Don't tell anyone.

394
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:06,400
Is that clear?

395
00:23:06,467 --> 00:23:07,500
Emma?

396
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:09,800
Yes, I got it.

397
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:22,167
Mom, what is that for?

398
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:24,033
Antispasmodic.

399
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:28,067
So what it does, it reduces
the effects of your bowel

400
00:23:28,133 --> 00:23:29,600
and bladder control.

401
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:32,133
Remember, I'm a doctor.

402
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,533
I know what I'm doing.

403
00:23:34,567 --> 00:23:36,367
Double lock Mookie's room.

404
00:23:36,433 --> 00:23:39,167
Make sure she can't
go out of her room.

405
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:44,633
Whatever you hear or see there,
don't ever get involved.

406
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,933
Mommy!

407
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:52,733
Mookie?

408
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:54,367
Mommy?
